The Federal Government has urged state governors to apply accountability mechanisms to the vaccination process and to develop daily, weekly and monthly Covid-19 and Childhood vaccination targets based on the total eligible populations across states.    The Executive Director, National Primary Healthcare Development Agency (NPHCDA), Dr. Faisal Shuaib who made the call today as the agency gives update on Covid 19 vaccination across the country in Abuja, explained that in this phase of COVID-19 mass vaccination there are plan underway to integrate the campaign with childhood immunization and other primary health care services.   On the vaccination process so far, the Executive Director informed that as of today, Tuesday January 25th 2022 14,093,873 eligible persons have received the first dose of COVID-19 vaccine in Nigeria while 5,252,406 eligible Nigerians have been fully vaccinated.   He further noted that so far the booster dose of COVID-19 vaccine that was recommended by WHO for people who have received two doses of AstraZeneca, Moderna, Pfizer Bio-N-Tech or one dose of Johnson & Johnson vaccines, 416,980 Nigerians have received the booster shot.